{"schemaVersion":1,"bookId":"situational-15000","unitId":"scene-282","title":"时装表演","sectionId":"chapter-12","sectionTitle":"休闲娱乐无极限","pageStart":1374,"pageEnd":1377,"extractionMethod":"text-layer","wordEntryCount":24,"duplicateEntryCount":14,"pages":[{"number":1374,"blocks":[{"type":"title","text":"282 时装表演"},{"type":"section","text":"Step1 场景词"},{"type":"entry","text":"fashion show 时装秀","headword":"fashion show"},{"type":"entry","text":"Fashion Week 时装周","headword":"Fashion Week"},{"type":"entry","text":"Paris [ˈpærɪs]","headword":"Paris"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.巴黎"},{"type":"entry","text":"Milan [mɪˈlæn]","headword":"Milan"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.米兰"},{"type":"entry","text":"London [ˈlʌndən]","headword":"London"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.伦敦"},{"type":"entry","text":"New York 纽约","headword":"New York"},{"type":"entry","text":"fashion designer 时装设计师","headword":"fashion designer"}]},{"number":1375,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"catwalk [ˈkætwɔːk]","headword":"catwalk"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.猫步；T台"},{"type":"entry","text":"fashion collection时装系列","headword":"fashion collection"},{"type":"entry","text":"apparel [əˈpærəl]","headword":"apparel"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.服装"},{"type":"entry","text":"craftsmanship [ˈkrɑːftsmənʃɪp]","headword":"craftsmanship"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.手艺，技艺"},{"type":"entry","text":"design inspiration设计灵感","headword":"design inspiration"},{"type":"entry","text":"intellectual creativity创造性，创造力","headword":"intellectual creativity"},{"type":"entry","text":"high fashion 高级时装；高级时尚","headword":"high fashion"}]},{"number":1376,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"fashion industry 时尚产业；时装产业","headword":"fashion industry"},{"type":"entry","text":"fashion magazine 时尚杂志；时装杂志","headword":"fashion magazine"},{"type":"entry","text":"commercial performance 商演","headword":"commercial performance"},{"type":"entry","text":"fashion icon 时尚偶像","headword":"fashion icon"},{"type":"entry","text":"super star 超级明星，大牌明星","headword":"super star"},{"type":"entry","text":"luxury goods 奢侈品","headword":"luxury goods"},{"type":"entry","text":"high class 高级","headword":"high class"}]},{"number":1377,"blocks":[{"type":"entry","text":"mark [mɑːk]","headword":"mark"},{"type":"definition","text":"n.标志"},{"type":"section","text":"Step2 学以致用"},{"type":"text","text":"有趣的小词shape"},{"type":"text","text":"1. You are in good shape. 你的身体状况不错。"},{"type":"entry","text":"In good shape的意思是“处于良好状态，健康状况良好”，相当于in","headword":"In good shape"},{"type":"text","text":"good condition。反之，in bad/poor shape指身体状况不佳，例如：The"},{"type":"text","text":"illness has left him in rather poor shape.（他经过这场大病已形容枯"},{"type":"text","text":"槁。）"},{"type":"text","text":"2. I don't know how my weekend is going to shape up yet. 我还不知道周"},{"type":"text","text":"末要做什么。"},{"type":"entry","text":"Shape up有“形成；进展”的意思，例如：How is the new team","headword":"Shape up"},{"type":"text","text":"shaping up?（新队伍的表现怎样？）shape up还有“表现良好”的意思。"},{"type":"text","text":"如果你在工作中表现不好，老板就会对你说You'd better shape up if you"},{"type":"text","text":"want to stay on.（如果你还想留下来的话最好还是表现好一点儿。）经"},{"type":"text","text":"常听到长辈对我们说“年轻人，你要好自为之。”这句话用英语表达就"},{"type":"text","text":"是You'd better shape up, young man。"}]}]}